{
  "text": "ADAMTS-1 is the first member of the disintegrin-like and metalloproteinase with thrombospondin type I motifs (ADAMTS) family, and is characterized by having an ADAM metalloproteinase domain and thrombospondin type I motifs [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . ADAMTS-1 was originally identified as a gene strongly expressed in cachexigenic tumors [CITATION_3] . ADAMTS-1 consists of proprotein-, metalloproteinaseand disintegrin-like domains, thrombospondin type I motifs and intervening spacer region among them.",
